      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "AZIONE (4) broke through for the first win of the preparation at his latest appearance when he scored by 22 metres over 2130m at this track after having raced three-wide without cover at the bell. Recent effort is good enough to win a race of this calibre. CANELO (9) found a couple better two runs back then made mistakes last time when he broke and finished 7 metres back in fifth over 1730m at this track. The driver has some work to do from this wide starting position. Meets a similar line up so he is sure to be a force if the manners improve. MAD PUNTA (7) finished eighth over 2130m at this track as the favourite last start after getting held-up for a run over the final stages. With better luck today can make amends. DANGER (8) is the next elect off a last-start win by one metre at this track over 1730m.",
